cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY 

This paper focuses on studying the unique behaviors of Chinese microblogging users, specifically on Tencent Weibo. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also analyzes user actions and social influence, which falls under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). Additionally, the paper uses natural language processing techniques to analyze the content of microblogs, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses information diffusion, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the cultural differences between Chinese and Western microblogging users, which falls under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
